I’m reposting two things I posted last thread because they didn’t get much responses and I want to see what other people think of them. First off: this comment on overrated stories, specifically Were It Not For You, because I find this story to be really interesting and I just think there were so many other ways this story could’ve been done and it’s disappointing.

I also didn’t like how in Were It Not For You, because everything seemingly just works out. I wanted more drama with Anon. Maybe it would be better if he didn’t connect with the waifur so fast. He started out hating anthros right? And then he just... stops hating them all of a sudden? That didn’t make sense to me.

If I were to recreate Were It Not For You, I would make it less a romance and more a story of a waifur who was a saved by a human and how she tries to break him out of his shell. His “shell” being his hatred for anthros (which doesn’t just magically go away like in the actual story), his previous homelessness and drug use, and years of being away from his family, who he will never see again. Romance would not even be an idea until the end, it would be much more cynical and focus on the worse aspects of Anon’s character.
